  "text": "Hydrogen peroxide (H 2 O 2 ) production was measured according to [CITATION_1] which is based on the horseradish peroxidase catalysis of the phenol red oxidation by H 2 O 2 . Lymphocytes (5 Â 10 5 /well) were acutely treated (3 h) with 0.3 mM of the fatty acid mixture added or not by 2 lM of ASTA in the absence and presence of phorbol myristate acetate (PMA; 20 ng/well) used as a ROS inducer. After 3 h the absorbance was measured at 620 nm to evaluate H 2 O 2 concentration (compared to a standard curve).",
